INC-2026-CHANGEORG-LIVE-PETITION-DEGRADED-STARTER-BLOCK

## Date
2026-03-27

## Status
Open

## Severity
Medium-High

## Prepared By
Magical Lobster

## Summary

A live public Change.org petition remains publicly discoverable at `https://www.change.org/p/facts-of-law-state-of-vermont-s-misclassification-leads-to-failed-prosecution-of-gamache`. The petition page itself appears live and publicly accessible. However, the petition-starter identity block appears degraded, anonymized, or otherwise reduced at the presentation layer, displaying `N A` rather than a normal identifiable starter profile.

This incident should be tracked as a distinct live third-party petition-surface issue. It is not a stale dead-link artifact, and it should not be treated as equivalent to a fully intact live third-party profile page.

## Source Type
Live third-party petition page

## Page Type
Canonical public petition surface

## Risk Class
Live third-party identity-association surface with degraded starter-profile presentation

## Findings

### 1. The petition page remains live

The petition URL remains a publicly discoverable live page rather than a dead route, removed artifact, or broken shell.

### 2. The starter identity block appears degraded

The captured page state reflects a starter identity presentation of `N A` rather than a standard identifiable starter display. The role label `Petition Starter` remains visible, but the associated starter identity layer appears reduced, anonymized, detached, or otherwise degraded.

### 3. The page remains a third-party public surface despite the degraded starter block

The degraded starter identity block does not eliminate the page’s status as a live public third-party petition surface. The page should therefore continue to be treated as an active discovery surface, even if the profile-associated presentation has been partially diminished.

### 4. Exact root cause remains unconfirmed

The currently observed state is consistent with presentation-layer anonymization, profile detachment, partial account removal, or similar display degradation. The available evidence supports documenting the degraded state, but not overclaiming the exact underlying cause.

## Why This Matters

This incident matters because it reflects a mixed condition:

- the petition page remains publicly live and discoverable;
- the associated starter identity block appears degraded rather than fully intact;
- the surface therefore sits between a fully intact third-party profile-linked page and a dead or stale route.

That mixed condition should be tracked separately so the record accurately reflects both persistence and degradation.

## Impact

This page may continue to support:

- public petition-surface discovery;
- title-level or URL-level search visibility;
- persistence of third-party public association;
- partial identity ambiguity caused by degraded starter presentation.

Because the page remains live, it should not be misclassified as resolved merely because one visible identity component appears degraded.

## Desired End State

- Reduce or eliminate search visibility of the live petition page where it persists.
- Preserve technical documentation that the petition surface remains live while the starter identity block appears degraded.
- Maintain separate classification from:
  - stale dead-route incidents; and
  - fully intact live third-party profile pages.

